-- Algebra/escalation.math
--
-- The escalation step (fifteen-theorem stage S3.E1). An escalation of a
-- form A is a symmetric positive-definite extension of A by one basis
-- vector whose norm is the truant of A — the bordered Gram matrix
-- [[A, b], [bᵀ, truant(A)]]. An escalation represents the truant (at the
-- new basis vector), and the Cauchy–Schwarz entry bound confines its
-- border column to the explicit box b_i² < A(i,i)·truant(A) — so each
-- escalation step searches a finite, explicitly bounded set of forms.

module Algebra.escalation

